dataElementConceptDetails.definition: A benign or malignant tissue growth resulting from uncontrolled cell proliferation.  Benign neoplastic cells resemble normal cells without exhibiting significant cytologic atypia, while malignant cells exhibit overt signs such as dysplastic features, atypical mitotic figures, necrosis, nuclear pleomorphism, and anaplasia.  Representative examples of benign neoplasms include papillomas, cystadenomas, and lipomas; malignant neoplasms include carcinomas, sarcomas, lymphomas, and leukemias._Any abnormal condition of the body or mind that causes discomfort, dysfunction, or distress to the person affected or those in contact with the person. The term is often used broadly to include injuries, disabilities, syndromes, symptoms, deviant behaviors, and atypical variations of structure and function._Named locations of or within the body.

permissibleValues.meaningDescription: The thickened bony structures in the mandible and maxilla that contain the sockets of the teeth.
permissibleValues.vmDescription: The thickened bony structures in the mandible and maxilla that contain the sockets of the teeth.

permissibleValues.meaningDescription: Distal; situated farthest from a point of attachment or origin, as of a limb or bone; or directed away from the midline or mesial plane of the body.: A chamber formation in an organ.

permissibleValues.meaningDescription: Ascending Colon
permissibleValues.vmDescription: The first part of the colon (large intestine) that starts in the right lower quadrant of the abdomen and ends at the transverse colon in the right upper quadrant of the abdomen.

permissibleValues.meaningDescription: No Value Exists
permissibleValues.vmDescription: The posterior one third of the tongue behind the terminal sulcus that forms the anterior aspect of the oro-pharynx responsible for swallowing and modification of the voice in speech.

permissibleValues.vmDescription: The part of the pancreas from the point where it crosses the portal vein to the point where it enters the lienorenal ligament.

permissibleValues.meaningDescription: Bone Name
permissibleValues.vmDescription: Connective tissue that forms the skeletal components of the body.

permissibleValues.meaningDescription: Brain
permissibleValues.vmDescription: An organ composed of grey and white matter containing billions of neurons that is the center for intelligence and reasoning. It is protected by the bony cranium.

permissibleValues.meaningDescription: Of, or pertaining to, the bronchus.
permissibleValues.vmDescription: Of, or pertaining to, the bronchus.

permissibleValues.meaningDescription: Bronchus, specify
permissibleValues.vmDescription: Tubular structure in continuation with the trachea, serving as air passage. It terminates in the lung (terminal bronchiole).

permissibleValues.meaningDescription: The mucosal membranes located on the inside of the cheek, in the buccal cavity.
permissibleValues.vmDescription: The mucosal membranes located on the inside of the cheek, in the buccal cavity.

permissibleValues.meaningDescription: Proximal; situated nearest to a point of attachment or origin.: The area around the esophagogastric mucosal junction where the esophageal mucosa transitions into the gastric mucosa.
permissibleValues.vmDescription: Proximal; situated nearest to a point of attachment or origin.: The area around the esophagogastric mucosal junction where the esophageal mucosa transitions into the gastric mucosa.

permissibleValues.meaningDescription: Descending Colon
permissibleValues.vmDescription: The fourth portion of the large intestine (colon) that communicates with the transverse colon in the left-upper quadrant of the abdomen and the rectum below.

permissibleValues.meaningDescription: Refers to cancer that has spread from the original (primary) tumor to distant organs or distant lymph nodes.
permissibleValues.vmDescription: Refers to cancer that has spread from the original (primary) tumor to distant organs or distant lymph nodes.
Body limbs, consisting of right upper and lower (arm and leg) and left upper and lower (arm and leg).
The area of the mouth under the ventral surface of the tongue.

permissibleValues.meaningDescription: The entire physical structure of an organism.  It is composed of anatomic systems, regions, cavities, and spaces.: The larger part of a hollow organ that is farthest away from the organ's opening. The bladder, gallbladder, stomach, uterus, eye, and cavity of the middle ear all have a fundus.
permissibleValues.vmDescription: The entire physical structure of an organism.  It is composed of anatomic systems, regions, cavities, and spaces.: The bottom portion or the portion that is furthest from the opening of a hollow organ.

permissibleValues.meaningDescription: The anatomical location where the esophagus joins to the stomach.
permissibleValues.vmDescription: The anatomical location where the esophagus joins to the stomach.

permissibleValues.meaningDescription: The bony anterior part of the roof of the mouth separating the nose from the mouth.
permissibleValues.vmDescription: The bony anterior part of the roof of the mouth separating the nose from the mouth.

permissibleValues.meaningDescription: For oncology, area of the body generally construed to comprise base of skull and facial bones, sinuses, orbits, salivary glands, oral cavity, oropharynx, larynx, thyroid, facial and neck musculature and lymph nodes draining these areas.
permissibleValues.vmDescription: For oncology, area of the body generally construed to comprise base of skull and facial bones, sinuses, orbits, salivary glands, oral cavity, oropharynx, larynx, thyroid, facial and neck musculature and lymph nodes draining these areas.

permissibleValues.meaningDescription: That portion of the pancreas lying in the concavity of the duodenum.
permissibleValues.vmDescription: That portion of the pancreas lying in the concavity of the duodenum.

permissibleValues.meaningDescription: The bend of the colon at the juncture of its ascending and transverse portions.
permissibleValues.vmDescription: The bend of the colon at the juncture of its ascending and transverse portions.

permissibleValues.meaningDescription: The portion of the pharynx between the inferior portion of the oropharynx and the larynx.
permissibleValues.vmDescription: The portion of the pharynx between the inferior portion of the oropharynx and the larynx.

permissibleValues.meaningDescription: The cartilaginous structure of the respiratory tract between the pharynx and the trachea. It contains elastic vocal cords required for sound production.
permissibleValues.vmDescription: The cartilaginous structure of the respiratory tract between the pharynx and the trachea. It contains elastic vocal cords required for sound production.

permissibleValues.meaningDescription: Fleshy fold which surrounds the opening of the mouth.
permissibleValues.vmDescription: Fleshy fold which surrounds the opening of the mouth.

permissibleValues.meaningDescription: A triangular-shaped organ located under the diaphragm in the right hypochondrium. It is the largest internal organ of the body, weighting up to 2 kg. Metabolism and bile secretion are its main functions. It is composed of cells which have the ability to regenerate.
permissibleValues.vmDescription: A triangular-shaped organ located under the diaphragm in the right hypochondrium. It is the largest internal organ of the body, weighting up to 2 kg. Metabolism and bile secretion are its main functions. It is composed of cells which have the ability to regenerate.

One of a pair of viscera occupying the pulmonary cavities of the thorax, the organs of respiration in which aeration of the blood takes place. As a rule, the right lung is slightly larger than the left and is divided into three lobes (an upper, a middle, and a lower or basal), while the left has but two lobes (an upper and a lower or basal). Each lung is irregularly conical in shape, presenting a blunt upper extremity (the apex), a concave base following the curve of the diaphragm, an outer convex surface (costal surface), an inner or mediastinal surface (mediastinal surface), a thin and sharp anterior border, and a thick and rounded posterior border.

permissibleValues.meaningDescription: The cavity lying at the upper end of the alimentary canal, bounded on the outside by the lips and inside by the oropharynx and containing in humans the tongue, gums, and teeth.
permissibleValues.vmDescription: The cavity lying at the upper end of the alimentary canal, bounded on the outside by the lips and inside by the oropharynx and containing in humans the tongue, gums, and teeth.

permissibleValues.meaningDescription: The muscular organ located in the floor of the mouth and serving as the principal organ of taste and modification of the voice in speech.
permissibleValues.vmDescription: The muscular organ located in the floor of the mouth and serving as the principal organ of taste and modification of the voice in speech.
(or-o-FAIR-inks) The middle part of the throat that includes the soft palate, the base of the tongue, and the tonsils.

permissibleValues.meaningDescription: Rectum
permissibleValues.vmDescription: The terminal portion of the gastrointestinal tract, extending from the rectosigmoid junction to the anal canal.

permissibleValues.vmDescription: The bend at the junction of the transverse and descending colon.

permissibleValues.vmDescription: The left extremity of the pancreas within the lienorenal ligament.

permissibleValues.vmDescription: The third division of the colon (large intestine). It communicates with the ascending colon in the upper right-hand quadrant of the abdomen and the descending colon in the upper left-hand quadrant.

permissibleValues.vmDescription: The body excluding the head and neck and limbs.
